@node intro "Introduction"

 The classical Sokoban game in 3D.
   
@endnode

@node install "Installation"

 It is very easy. Just copy the files where you want,
 but the program needs some @{" requirements " link require}!

@endnode

@node require "Requirements"
                    
        Requirements:
        -------------

	-one AMIGA :-)
	-PPC card
	-3D graphic card
	
	-OS3.0+
	-WarpOS V4
	-Warp3D V3
	-cybergraphics V3+

@endnode

@node use "Usage"
  
 Control: joystick port 2

 Window mode requires minimum 15-bit depth Workbench.
 The full screen mode requires minimum 15-bit screenmode.

 Game keys:   

   'f'   : fog on/off

   's'   : ScreenShot (ram:shot.ppm)

   'ESC' : quit
        
@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

 CLI arguments:

 -w: window/screen width
 -h: window/screen height
 -fs: full screen mode
 -bi: bilinear-filter off

 (Before start: STACK 1000000 !)
     
@endnode

@node bugs "Know Bugs"
        
 If you start the game in full screen mode and there is no
 suitable screenmode for -w and -h, the border will flashing.

 If you find a bug, please write the @{"author" link author }.

 Tested with:
	A1200
	BlizzardPPC 603/240 040/25 32M RAM
	BVisionPPC
	WarpOS V4
	Warp3D V3
	Cybergraphics V3

@endnode

